===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}}, from {{etyl|LL.}}, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|Ἀβαδδών||Abaddon|tr=Abaddōn|lang=grc}}, from {{etyl|he}} {{term|אבדון|lang=he}} ''ābaddōn'', destruction, abyss, from {{Hebr|[[אבד]]}} ''ābad'', to be lost, to [[perish]].

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun|s}}

# The [[destroyer]], or angel of the [[bottomless]] pit; -- the same as [[Apollyon]] and [[Asmodeus]].
# {{poetic}} Hell; the bottomless pit.
#*: In all her gates, ''Abaddon'' rues Thy bold attempt. - [[w:John Milton|John Milton]]

